The paper focuses on fine-grained action detection, which is a task commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning spatio-temporal features, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). The task of action detection also has applications in robotics (cs.RO) and human-computer interaction (cs.MM).
